  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">A second chance for teenage mothers in Tanzania</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In Tanzania girls who become pregnant, even by rape, forfeit any right to an education in government schools. Most cannot afford a private education. We are setting up a new inclusive and stigma free learning center in Tabora, Tanzania to help these girls regain their education goals and eventually access higher education, vocational and other technical training. Such Alternative Education Pathways (AEPs) are a proven model of enabling teenage mothers to continue an education.</narrative>
  </description>
